I've been trying to resolve some of the issues and making some progress.  The page I posted above has different issues to the ones I'm experiencing on the live build.

The live environment builds the table content from a socket feed, jquery.tablesorter.combined.js was erroring on line 4068, it turns out that the array setFilters was 0 length and was trying to reference the 0 element.

I added:

            if ( setFilters.length ) {
              var objFilter = setFilters[ i ];
              
              if ( objFilter != undefined ) { 
						    $column.val( objFilter ).trigger( 'change.tsfilter' );
              }
            }

This resolved the error and the pager now renders correctly.  However now, with just 1 item in the table, the headers do not line up with the columns.

Ahh yes, that is another issue with the css... Now, when a column has it's sort disabled, a class name of "sorter-false" is added. If you look at the "theme.blue.css" file you'll find this line:

```css
.tablesorter-blue thead .sorter-false {
	background-image: none;
	cursor: default;
	padding: 4px;
}
```

Which removes the background image from the header and changes the cursor back to an arrow.

In the next iteration of tablesorter, which is named [Abelt](https://github.com/tablesort/Abelt) to avoid confusing this fork with the original tablesorter, the icons will only target the `<i>` element within the header.

